info:
The Arista EOS content pack provides detailed monitoring and alerts for your Arista EOS devices. With the addition of the Arista Log Insight extension, additional switch monitoring beyond standard switch syslog output is available.

NOTE: To fully leverage the power of this content pack the Arista Log Insight extension needs to be installed on your switches.  Only basic functionality is available with the standard syslog settings. Please contact your Arista representative for details.

This content pack includes the following dashboards:

Overview: A high level summary of events, warnings, and errors across your network. Alerts can be triggered on emergency events that need immediate attention.

Inventory: Track the switches and transceivers currently deployed in your network.

Interface Counters / Errors: Monitor traffic statistics and interface errors.  Trigger alerts based on interface error events.

Platform Information: Track environmental data such as power and temperature. The alerts can notify an administrator of platform issues.

Virtualization: Gain visibility into VMware vMotion events and NSX logical switches on the network.

Layer 3 Routing: Monitor BGP and OSPF errors on the network.
name: Arista - EOS
author: Arista Networks, Inc.

info:
Brocade SAN content pack helps the user to better search, analyze and manage the log data generated by  Brocade SAN. Content pack can be used in two ways:
- Configure BNA to forward syslogs from all the switches of interest, to Log Insight
- Configure switches to forward syslog to Log Insight

author: Brocade

info:
The content pack for Nexus switches offers easy to understand, visual representation on how well operationally, the Nexus switches are working. The content pack sorts the log messages collected by feature and technology type, for quick simple representation of messages by severity level, and the impact of these operationally.
 
The Nexus Switching content pack collects and organizes the Log messages based upon the type and priority of the message and stores these into the database for time of day analysis. The Log Insight system administrator can then view the log messages by networking functions including routing, switching, security, access, authentication, as well as the more common device and interface type, for researching and remediating problems.
 
The content pack has 12 dashboards, 68 widgets, 13 queries , and X alarms specific to Nexus switches. Both Nexus fixed and modular chassis are supported including the Nexus 2K, 3K, 5K, 6K and 7K. More notable features include reporting on security, device, topology, and performance events that impact the operations of the data center network.
name: Cisco - Nexus
author: VMware

info:
The UCS content pack contains critical information about everything within a UCS system from UCS Central and UCS Manager down to chassis, blades, and networking components. The content pack provides:

Component Faults and Reasons
When hardware issues are detected, quickly investigate and resolve them.

Configuration Changes and Faults
Quickly identify what configuration changes have occurred over time and get notification of configuration faults immediately.

Authentication Requests
Track user sessions from both the GUI and the CLI including failed log in attempts and authentication sources.

The UCS content pack is a powerful monitoring tool for UCS environments, making you aware of any issues quickly and allowing you to maintain a healthy environment at all times.
name: Cisco - UCS
author: Cisco Systems, Inc.

info:
The Log Insight General Content Pack includes four dashboards:

• Overview - Provides generic information about any events being sent to your Log Insight instance including errors, warnings, and exceptions.
• Event Types - Provides information discovered by Log Insight's machine learning including unique errors, warnings, and exceptions.
• Agents - Provides information about configured Log Insight agents including configured filelog and winlog collection. For information about currently configured agents, visit the Agents page.

info:
The .NET Framework provides a run-time environment called the common language runtime (CLR), which runs the code and provides services that make the development process easier.
The content pack for Microsoft .NET CLR provides you with information about key entities of .NET CLR ETW events including various tasks and alarms using vCenter Log Insight's ability to monitor event logs.
The content pack covers the following:
General overview:
The widgets in this dashboard describe event tracing for Windows (ETW) events. Each event has an associated keyword and level, which are described in the CLR ETW Keywords and Levels topic.
It covers various events grouped by ETW keyword along with various exception, loader and security events.
The dashboard has an additional query widget which lists queries that provide more information about the CLR events.
Detailed analysis of Garbage Collection, Runtime Information, Contention and Thread Pool Events:
The content pack has 4 dashboards with a total of 26 widgets which give you a detailed analysis of these various ETW events.
Additional information:
• Query notes: Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget with links to documentation, knowledge base articles, and any other information making it possible to understand the data presented.
 
For more information visit : http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dd264810(v=vs.110).aspx
name: Microsoft - .NET CLR
author: VMware,Inc.

info:
The content pack for Microsoft® Active Directory® provides you with information about key entities of any AD installation’s health using vCenter Log Insight’s ability to monitor Windows® Event Logs.  The content pack enables:

Focus on known problems through monitoring events raised in the Windows Event Log.
 
Key AD components are covered—AD security, AD DS, DFS, and DNS
Eight dashboards containing 37 widgets are included from AD security, AD DS, DFS, and DNS that go in depth to quantify your data in a multitude of manners to help diagnose problems in your AD infrastructure. 
 
Employs features added in Log Insight 2.0

info:
The content pack for Microsoft SQL Server provides you with information about key entities of any MS SQL server including various tasks and alarms using vCenter Log Insight's ability to monitor event logs.
The content pack enables:
General overview and connection related events of MS SQL server:
This dashboard gives information about various errors encountered in MS SQL server along with the severity and state of the error. This also enables you to monitor the sessions/connections  over time.
This also helps in monitoring the logins to the SQL server and alert the database administrator in case of multiple failed login attempts.
Corruption, Deadlock Issues:
This dashboard alerts the administrator and gives a detailed view of various corruption events such as database corruption, index corruption etc. User can also enable the alarm for transaction deadlock related issues where resources are deadlocked and the queries have to be rerun.
Server related errors and invalid queries:
MS SQL server can encounter various media failure and database engine software related errors.
Here you can monitor the various server related issues and raise an alarm to rectify it. Along with this you can also see errors related to insufficient resources, and invalid queries.
name: Microsoft - SQL Server
author: VMWare,Inc.

info:
The Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS content pack provides you with powerful insight into your PAN-OS logs (currently SYSTEM, CONFIG and THREAT; TRAFFIC and HIP-MATCH will be added in a later version of the content pack).
 
Log Field Definitions
 
Each standard field for each of the log types is defined, allowing you to easily perform queries using any of the fields.
 
Field names are in the format:
 
pan_{log,system,config,threat}_fieldname
 
pan_log_fieldname is used for the fixed location fields that are common to all the log types, and includes: receive_time, serial, type, subtype and time_generated.
 
pan_{system,config,threat}_fieldname is used for a field specific to the SYSTEM, CONFIG and THREAT logs.
 
Descriptions for each field can be found “Syslog Field Descriptions” section in the PAN-OS Administrator’s Guide:

https://paloaltonetworks.com/documentation/61/pan-os/pan-os/section_6/chapter_38.html
 
Configuring PAN-OS to Forward Logs to Log Insight

You will need to configure each firewall to forward its logs to Log Insight for analysis, or alternatively forward logs to Panorama and then forward to Log Insight.
 
To configure log forwarding to external hosts refer to the “Forward Logs to External Services” section in the PAN-OS Administrator’s Guide:

https://www.paloaltonetworks.com/documentation/61/pan-os/pan-os/section_6/chapter_20.html
name: Palo Alto Networks - PAN-OS
author: Palo Alto Networks, Inc.

info:
NSX-vSphere Content Pack provides powerful filtering, logging visualization and alerting of NSX for vSphere real-time operational activities.  This enables users to effectively monitor NSX-vSphere production installations using intuitive Log Insight UI dashboard widgets with just a couple clicks.

Highlights:

Easy, at a glance, views of an entire NSX-vSphere environment and components.  Users will know at a glance whether there is a problem with a NSX-vSphere environment by simply looking at the Overview dashboard.

The Content Pack highlights many areas of a NSX-vSphere environment including:
    Common Installation / Configuration issues - exposes several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations
    Logical Switch - exposes system logs, audit logs and several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations
    Logical Router - exposes system logs, audit logs and several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations
    Distributed Firewall - contains several different dashboards to exposes firewall traffic by total aggregate traffic, hypervisors and ruleIds
    Edge Services - separates logs for Edge appliance, health check, communication agent, high availability, load balancer, firewall and Ipsec VPN services
    Edge Firewall - contains several widgets for monitoring firewall traffic

To Setup - forward all logging components to the Log Insight server including:
    1. Use the Log Insight vSphere integration to forward logs for all ESXi servers
    2. NSX-vSphere Manager
    3. NSX-vSphere Controller(s)
    4. All NSX-vSphere edge devices

Where to begin:
    The NSX-vSphere - Overview is the main entry point.  This dashboard displays all problems/alerts reflected in the entire Content Pack, therefore under normal operating circumstances the dashboard should not contain any data.  Once a log appears on a widget, read the widget's information ("i"icon) in order to navigate to the appropriate dashboard for more detailed information associated with the problem.
    Additionally the Firewall dashboards provide widgets that contain many different views of firewall data.  These visualizations are aggregated to show various slices of a NSX-vSphere environment at the hypervisor, vm and application level.

Compatibility:
    Content Pack is compatible with NSX-vSphere 6.1.x
name: VMware - NSX-vSphere
author: VMware Inc.

info:
The vSphere content pack provides powerful insight into your vSphere logs, allowing you to make informed and proactive decisions within your environment.

IMPORTANT: To fully leverage the power of this content packs both vSphere integration and vRealize Operations integration is required.

This content pack enables:

Proactive monitoring of your vSphere environment

• Quickly identify issues: The General - Problems dashboard gives you a single pane of glass to find problems in your vSphere environment.
• Drill down to determine the root cause: Dashboard filters make it easy to see logs from specific parts of your vSphere environment.
• Easily consume data: Powerful and dynamic visualizations make it possible to detect anomalies, perform trending analysis, and pinpoint specific issues through targeted queries.
• Alerts: Know what to monitor in your vSphere logs and get notified when such events are detected.

Track changes and isolate security threats

• Configuration management: Track user-initiated changes and automated vSphere actions through the vCenter Server - Tasks and General - Configuration dashboards.
• Environmental changes: See what VMs are being moved through DRS and HA actions.
• Auditing: The General - Security dashboard allows you to find who is logging into vSphere devices from which locations and through what means.

Additional information and context

• Query notes: Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget with links to documentation, knowledge base articles, and any other information making it possible to understand the data presented.
• Inventory: The General - Inventory dashboard quantifies results seen through vSphere logs making it simple to ensure complete environment monitoring.
name: VMware - vSphere
author: VMware, Inc.
